ἓ 16. The formula of the next type is noun A, noun B, adj. A, adj. B. I have noted a parallel in Tacitus Ann. 1. 1 cuncta discordiis sessa civilibus. The type in parallel order (α) occurs first in Odes 1. 6. 13 Martem tunica tectum adamantina. The ehiastic type (β) is seen at Odes 3. 7. 13 Proetum mulier perfida credulum. Add 3. 24. 3, 4, and Epod. 8. 11, 12.

Under this section may come Odes 4. 8. 23, 24 where Romuli is equivalent to Romalis (adj.), and Epod. 13. 6 where consule is the equivalent of an adjective.
